snippet.textDisplay:
AN OWN GOAL PERHAPS!

THIS AIRCRAFT WAS A BOEING 737-800 AND WAS 3 YEARS OLD AT
THE TIME OF THE CRASH. The aircraft had its first flight on 21 June 2016
and was delivered to the airline on 19 July 2016.




A spokesperson from Iran's Road and Transportation Ministry
claims that the aircraft burst into flames after a fire started in one of its
engines, causing the pilot to lose control and crash into the ground. The
Ukrainian Embassy in Iran stated that preliminary details pointed to an engine
failure; it also issued a statement ruling out terrorism, BUT QUICKLY
REMOVED THE STATEMENT WITHOUT EXPLANATION.




The disaster occurred amid a heightened political crisis
between the United States and Iran in the Persian Gulf, happening just hours
after the Iranian military launched 15 rockets at U.S military airbases in Iraq
in response to the Baghdad International Airport airstrike by the US on 3
January. IN THE EARLY HOURS AFTER THE INCIDENT, IRANIAN TWITTER PROFILES
POSTED UNSUBSTANTIATED CLAIMS OF THE CRASH HAVING BEEN CAUSED BY AN
ANTI-AIRCRAFT MISSILE ERRONEOUSLY LAUNCHED BY THE IRANIAN MILITARY.




Al-Hadath, a Dubai-based news channel, claimed that
anti-aircraft missiles had shot down the aircraft.




The ISNA and other Iranian state news agencies, however,
reported that the plane was facing technical difficulties.




In the immediate aftermath of the crash, Ukrainian President
Volodymyr Zelensky stated that there should not be any speculations about the
cause of the crash.
